        "created_at": "2022-09-05T15:55:19.194Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Here\u2019s the 2018\u2019s I\u2019ve opened, some multiple times, and brief opinion. Overall the vintage has been good to me. I skipped Ramonet in 2018, which is unusual for me. I can\u2019t remember why, but must have used some convoluted logic at the time? I realize I\u2019m off topic (this is about Ramonet), but likely this thread will get a lot of \u201c2018\u201d attention so thought I\u2019d post this.<br>\nLafon Perrieres - love it.<br>\nLafon Poruzots - variable but overall very good.<br>\nLafon Montrachet - stunning.<br>\nLafon Genevrieres - delightful.<br>\nJadot Corton Charlemagne - a chameleon but should be good with time.<br>\nRoulot Corton Charlemagne - very good.<br>\nCoche Meursault - good, but shared one bottle with six so limited data.</p>",
